<subSubSection id="C3076564FFA9FF9EFF23DC2DE3C8E874" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BA236EFFFA9FF9EFF23DC2DE35EE995" blockId="11.[189,311,635,661]" box="[189,311,635,661]" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">
<heading id="D0EA8183FFA9FF9EFF23DC2DE35EE995" bold="true" box="[189,311,635,661]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B969EAFDFFA9FF9EFF23DC2DE35EE995" bold="true" box="[189,311,635,661]" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA236EFFFA9FF9EFF23DCFCE3C8E874" blockId="11.[189,1401,682,884]" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">
Males of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1D4D6CFFA9FF9EFEACDCFDE3FDE9C4" authority="Sánchez-Ruiz &amp; Martínez &amp; Bonaldo, 2022" authorityName="Sánchez-Ruiz &amp; Martínez &amp; Bonaldo" authorityYear="2022" box="[306,404,682,709]" class="Arachnida" family="Caponiidae" genus="Caponina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="huila" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B969EAFDFFA9FF9EFEACDCFDE3FDE9C4" box="[306,404,682,709]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">C. huila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25A5786FFA9FF9EFE02DCFDE391E9C5" box="[412,504,683,709]" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
resemble those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1D4D6CFFA9FF9EFD7FDCFDE108E9C4" authorityName="Platnick" authorityYear="1994" box="[737,865,683,709]" class="Arachnida" family="Caponiidae" genus="Caponina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paramo">
<emphasis id="B969EAFDFFA9FF9EFD7FDCFDE108E9C4" box="[737,865,683,709]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">C. paramo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by a large cymbium that is more than twice as long as the tibia length, and by a similar poorly pronounced dorsal tubercle on the palpal femur (
<figureCitation id="13262A6AFFA9FF9EFF58DCA6E357E80B" box="[198,318,752,779]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[191,234,1857,1883]" captionTargetBox="[249,1338,265,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-15@8.[249,1338,265,1819]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 3. A–B, E–G. Caponina bochalema sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3757). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. E. Left palp, retrolateral view. F. Left palp, ventral view. G. Left palp, prolateral view. – C–D, H–J. Caponina huila sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3761). C. Habitus, dorsal view. D. Habitus, ventral view. H. Left palp, retrolateral view. I. Left palp, ventral view. J. Left palp, prolateral view. Scale bars: A–D = 1.5 mm; E–J = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468230" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468230/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">Fig. 3H–J</figureCitation>
), but can be distinguished by having a anteriorly directed embolar base (
<figureCitation id="13262A6AFFA9FF9EFB0FDCA6E766E80B" box="[1169,1295,752,779]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[189,1319,768,1849]" captionTargetId="figure-165@9.[189,1398,761,1857]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. A–C. Caponina bochalema sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3757). A. Left palp, retrolateral view. B. Left palp, ventral view. C. Left palp, prolateral view. – D–F. Caponina huila sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3761). D. Left palp, retrolateral view. E. Left palp, ventral view. F. Left palp, prolateral view. Scale bars = 1 mm. Abbreviations: see Material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468234" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468234/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">Fig. 4D–F</figureCitation>
), instead posteriorly directed as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1D4D6CFFA9FF9EFE6ADD42E01CE82E" authorityName="Platnick" authorityYear="1994" box="[500,629,788,814]" class="Arachnida" family="Caponiidae" genus="Caponina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paramo">
<emphasis id="B969EAFDFFA9FF9EFE6ADD42E01CE82E" box="[500,629,788,814]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">C. paramo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8C4B1EFFA9FF9EFD24DD42E118E82E" author="Platnick N. I." box="[698,881,788,814]" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" pagination="1 - 15" refId="ref7090" refString="Platnick N. I. 1994 a. A revision of the spider genus Caponina (Araneae, Caponiidae). American Museum Novitates 3100: 1 - 15." type="journal article" year="1994">Platnick 1994a</bibRefCitation>
: figs 39–41). Additionally, the embolus tip is larger than that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1D4D6CFFA9FF9EFE20DD61E056E851" authorityName="Platnick" authorityYear="1994" box="[446,575,823,849]" class="Arachnida" family="Caponiidae" genus="Caponina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paramo">
<emphasis id="B969EAFDFFA9FF9EFE20DD61E056E851" box="[446,575,823,849]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">C. paramo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, presenting a median expansion, widening tip and enlarged opening (
<figureCitation id="13262A6AFFA9FF9EFF5BDD0CE328E874" box="[197,321,858,884]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[191,234,1857,1883]" captionTargetBox="[249,1338,265,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-15@8.[249,1338,265,1819]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 3. A–B, E–G. Caponina bochalema sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3757). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. E. Left palp, retrolateral view. F. Left palp, ventral view. G. Left palp, prolateral view. – C–D, H–J. Caponina huila sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3761). C. Habitus, dorsal view. D. Habitus, ventral view. H. Left palp, retrolateral view. I. Left palp, ventral view. J. Left palp, prolateral view. Scale bars: A–D = 1.5 mm; E–J = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468230" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468230/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">Figs 3H–J</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13262A6AFFA9FF9EFED3DD0CE3FCE874" box="[333,405,858,884]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[189,1319,768,1849]" captionTargetId="figure-165@9.[189,1398,761,1857]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. A–C. Caponina bochalema sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3757). A. Left palp, retrolateral view. B. Left palp, ventral view. C. Left palp, prolateral view. – D–F. Caponina huila sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3761). D. Left palp, retrolateral view. E. Left palp, ventral view. F. Left palp, prolateral view. Scale bars = 1 mm. Abbreviations: see Material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468234" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468234/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">4D–F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF626667FFA9FF9EFF23D9DEE1D3ECE8" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468240" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6468240" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468240/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" startId="11.[189,232,1928,1954]" targetBox="[209,1362,977,1880]" targetPageId="11">
<paragraph id="8BA236EFFFA9FF9EFF23D9DEE1D3ECE8" blockId="11.[188,1399,1928,2024]" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">
<emphasis id="B969EAFDFFA9FF9EFF23D9DEE364ECA2" bold="true" box="[189,269,1928,1954]" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">Fig. 6.</emphasis>
Distribution map of species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1D4D6CFFA9FF9EFD16D9DEE095ECA2" box="[648,764,1928,1954]" class="Arachnida" family="Caponiidae" genus="Caponina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B969EAFDFFA9FF9EFD16D9DEE095ECA2" box="[648,764,1928,1954]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">Caponina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<emphasis id="B969EAFDFFA9FF9EFC95D9DEE149ECA2" bold="true" box="[779,800,1928,1954]" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">A</emphasis>
. General distribution in the Neotropics, excluding Colombian species. 
<emphasis id="B969EAFDFFA9FF9EFE39D9FDE3D2ECC5" bold="true" box="[423,443,1963,1989]" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">B</emphasis>
. Distribution of Colombian species. Total extension of Andean cordillera in South American is represented in pink and Colombian Andes in yellow.
</paragraph>
</caption>
