<paragraph id="8BA236EFFFAEFF99FF23DC79E326E949" blockId="12.[189,335,559,585]" box="[189,335,559,585]" pageId="12" pageNumber="99">
<heading id="D0EA8183FFAEFF99FF23DC79E326E949" bold="true" box="[189,335,559,585]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="12" pageNumber="99" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B969EAFDFFAEFF99FF23DC79E326E949" bold="true" box="[189,335,559,585]" pageId="12" pageNumber="99">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA236EFFFAEFF99FF74DC0BE039E978" blockId="12.[189,1400,605,738]" box="[234,592,605,632]" pageId="12" pageNumber="99">
<emphasis id="B969EAFDFFAEFF99FF74DC0BE343E977" bold="true" box="[234,298,605,631]" pageId="12" pageNumber="99">Male</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus id="54A6884DFFAEFF99FEA4DC0BE3CCE977" box="[314,421,605,631]" pageId="12" pageNumber="99">holotype</typeStatus>
, IAvH-I 3761)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA236EFFFAEFF99FF23DCD7E14BE9E1" blockId="12.[189,1400,605,738]" pageId="12" pageNumber="99">
COLORATION. Carapace yellowish-orange (
<figureCitation id="13262A6AFFAEFF99FD35DCD6E164E99B" box="[683,781,640,667]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[191,234,1857,1883]" captionTargetBox="[249,1338,265,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-15@8.[249,1338,265,1819]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 3. A–B, E–G. Caponina bochalema sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3757). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. E. Left palp, retrolateral view. F. Left palp, ventral view. G. Left palp, prolateral view. – C–D, H–J. Caponina huila sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3761). C. Habitus, dorsal view. D. Habitus, ventral view. H. Left palp, retrolateral view. I. Left palp, ventral view. J. Left palp, prolateral view. Scale bars: A–D = 1.5 mm; E–J = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468230" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468230/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="99">Figs 3C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13262A6AFFAEFF99FC85DCD6E12AE99B" box="[795,835,640,667]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="10.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[187,1396,396,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-15@10.[187,1396,396,1853]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Fig. 5. A–B. Caponina alejandroi sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3747). A. Prosoma, dorsal view. B. Prosoma, ventral view. –C–D. Caponina bochalema sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3757). C. Prosoma, dorsal view. D. Prosoma, ventral view. – E–F. Caponina huila sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3761). E. Prosoma, dorsal view. F. Prosoma, ventral view. Scale bars = 1.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468236" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468236/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="99">5G</figureCitation>
). Chelicerae, endites, labium, sternum and legs yellowish-orange (
<figureCitation id="13262A6AFFAEFF99FE04DCF2E395E9BE" box="[410,508,676,702]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[191,234,1857,1883]" captionTargetBox="[249,1338,265,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-15@8.[249,1338,265,1819]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 3. A–B, E–G. Caponina bochalema sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3757). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. E. Left palp, retrolateral view. F. Left palp, ventral view. G. Left palp, prolateral view. – C–D, H–J. Caponina huila sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3761). C. Habitus, dorsal view. D. Habitus, ventral view. H. Left palp, retrolateral view. I. Left palp, ventral view. J. Left palp, prolateral view. Scale bars: A–D = 1.5 mm; E–J = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468230" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468230/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="99">Figs 3D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13262A6AFFAEFF99FD97DCF2E058E9BF" box="[521,561,676,703]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="10.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[187,1396,396,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-15@10.[187,1396,396,1853]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Fig. 5. A–B. Caponina alejandroi sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3747). A. Prosoma, dorsal view. B. Prosoma, ventral view. –C–D. Caponina bochalema sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3757). C. Prosoma, dorsal view. D. Prosoma, ventral view. – E–F. Caponina huila sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3761). E. Prosoma, dorsal view. F. Prosoma, ventral view. Scale bars = 1.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468236" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468236/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="99">5H</figureCitation>
). Abdomen pale beige (
<figureCitation id="13262A6AFFAEFF99FCD6DCF2E1A0E9BE" box="[840,969,676,702]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[191,234,1857,1883]" captionTargetBox="[249,1338,265,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-15@8.[249,1338,265,1819]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 3. A–B, E–G. Caponina bochalema sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3757). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. E. Left palp, retrolateral view. F. Left palp, ventral view. G. Left palp, prolateral view. – C–D, H–J. Caponina huila sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3761). C. Habitus, dorsal view. D. Habitus, ventral view. H. Left palp, retrolateral view. I. Left palp, ventral view. J. Left palp, prolateral view. Scale bars: A–D = 1.5 mm; E–J = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468230" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468230/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="99">Fig. 3C–D</figureCitation>
), covered by many dark, short setae, epigastric region pale orange. Spinnerets pale beige.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA236EFFFAEFF99FF23DD5FE1A6E846" blockId="12.[189,1398,776,838]" pageId="12" pageNumber="99">MEASUREMENTS. Total length 3.65, carapace 1.34 long, 1.17 wide, 0.38 high, sternum 0.85 long, 0.80 wide, legs: I: 3.51; II: 3.35; III: 2.76; IV: 4.16, abdomen 2.25 long.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA236EFFFAEFF99FF23DD38E1ADEF37" blockId="12.[188,1399,877,1079]" pageId="12" pageNumber="99">
MORPHOLOGY. Carapace flat with soft cuticle. Six eyes, AME the largest, dark, separated by about half their diameter, ALE pale translucent and smaller than AME, PLE pale translucent and smaller than ALE. Palpal femur with poorly developed dorsal tubercle and small prolateral stridulatory pick (
<figureCitation id="13262A6AFFAEFF99FA9BDDE5E70EE8CE" box="[1285,1383,947,974]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[191,234,1857,1883]" captionTargetBox="[249,1338,265,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-15@8.[249,1338,265,1819]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 3. A–B, E–G. Caponina bochalema sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3757). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. E. Left palp, retrolateral view. F. Left palp, ventral view. G. Left palp, prolateral view. – C–D, H–J. Caponina huila sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3761). C. Habitus, dorsal view. D. Habitus, ventral view. H. Left palp, retrolateral view. I. Left palp, ventral view. J. Left palp, prolateral view. Scale bars: A–D = 1.5 mm; E–J = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468230" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468230/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="99">Fig. 3H</figureCitation>
); cymbium more than twice as long as tibia, with rounded tip, tegulum oval, with long, thin embolus, protruding ventrally from approximately middle surface of tegulum and directed anteriorly, with median expansion, widening tip and enlarged opening (
<figureCitation id="13262A6AFFAEFF99FD76DA4BE10DEF37" box="[744,868,1053,1079]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[191,234,1857,1883]" captionTargetBox="[249,1338,265,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-15@8.[249,1338,265,1819]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 3. A–B, E–G. Caponina bochalema sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3757). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. E. Left palp, retrolateral view. F. Left palp, ventral view. G. Left palp, prolateral view. – C–D, H–J. Caponina huila sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3761). C. Habitus, dorsal view. D. Habitus, ventral view. H. Left palp, retrolateral view. I. Left palp, ventral view. J. Left palp, prolateral view. Scale bars: A–D = 1.5 mm; E–J = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468230" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468230/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="99">Figs 3H–J</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13262A6AFFAEFF99FCEEDA4BE1D1EF37" box="[880,952,1053,1079]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[189,1319,768,1849]" captionTargetId="figure-165@9.[189,1398,761,1857]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. A–C. Caponina bochalema sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3757). A. Left palp, retrolateral view. B. Left palp, ventral view. C. Left palp, prolateral view. – D–F. Caponina huila sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3761). D. Left palp, retrolateral view. E. Left palp, ventral view. F. Left palp, prolateral view. Scale bars = 1 mm. Abbreviations: see Material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468234" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468234/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="99">4D–F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA236EFFFAEFF99FF74DA09E32FEF79" blockId="12.[189,326,1119,1180]" box="[234,326,1119,1145]" pageId="12" pageNumber="99">
